The paper deals with sparse approximation problems, which are closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The introduction of list versions of these problems also involves machine learning and statistical inference (cs.LG). The paper also discusses uncertainty principles, which are relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
